 0758:         """
 0759:         The suction area is a lot smaller in the case of an offset 
 0760:         scroll wrap because it is only the part around where the scroll
 0761:         wraps come close to each other.  For crank angles from 0 to pi, 
 0762:         consider the cross-section to be approximately just half the circle that
 0763:         closes the involutes.  The diameter is the pitch minus the scroll thickness
 0764:         
 0765:         Beyond theta = pi, the area grows as the s1 chamber begins to compress
 0766:         The area remaining in the chamber at theta = 2*pi becomes the s1 chamber 
 0767:         """
